What a difference a day make, Don't take a timeless monument or anyone for granted. You always think this is something that can't happen until it happens in your own backyard. Paris and the world was heartbroken yesterday, Notre-Dame up in flames. No one was seriously hurt, we can all be thankful for that. I don't know about you but today Paris and the world is hopeful. The structure is still standing. It is strange to see Notre-Dame without a roof, without its spire, yet knowing It will be rebuilt makes us feel a little better today than yesterday. Thank you for all your kind words. Notre-Dame and its flying buttress in all their gothic splendour are still here for you to enjoy and take in.
